Francis Philip Francis (15 September 1852 – 18 January 1926) was an English cricketer.  Francis was a right-handed batsman who fielded as a wicket-keeper.  He was born in Upminster, Essex.
Francis made a single first-class appearance for Middlesex in 1881 against Surrey at Lord's.  In his only first-class match he wasn't required to bat or bowl.  He also played a number of matches for Essex before they were granted first-class status.He died in Claygate, Surrey on 18 January 1926.
